description: Site A of the wider Billet Road opportunity site - Demolition of all existing buildings on the site. Erection of 20no. single dwelling houses and blocks of flats of up to five storeys to contain 133no. self-contained flats (mixture of 1, 2, 3 and 4 bedrooms) with associated car and cycle parking, landscaping works, highways works and infrastructure works. This application is accompanied by an Environmental Statement. (AMENDED PLANS / DOCUMENTS - FOR FURTHER DETAILS PLEASE REFER TO THE COVER LETTER ONLINE DATED 23 SEPTEMBER 2024). (Summary).
site_name: Development At And Land West Of Hainault House
decision_conditions:
Prior to commencement of construction works, full details of the sound insulation and ventilation strategy shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, showing how the building has been designed to meet the following internal criteria: 
•	Living Rooms: 35 dB LAeq,16hr (between 07:00 and 23:00 hrs); 
•	Bedrooms: 30 dB LAeq,8hr (between 23:00 and 07:00 hrs); and 
•	Bedroom: 45 dB LAFmax to be exceeded no more than 10 times per night-time between 23:00 and 07:00 hours from sources other than emergency sirens. This is to be assessed as the maximum individual noise event in 5 minute periods during the period 2300hrs to 0700hrs.

The scheme shall be fully implemented in accordance with the approved details.

Reason: In order to protect the health and ensure quality of life enjoyed by future occupants of the development and to comply with Policies LP24 and LP26,and Policy D14 of the London Plan.
